<FIRST>r i AM-Colombia-Kidnapping     01-29 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Colombia-Kidnapping,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Psychologist, Colombian Industrialist Kidnapped, Police Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEDELLIN, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A heavily armed group has kidnapped an
American psychologist and Colombian industrialist in this city,
police said Saturday.
   Michael Ray, 36, of Philadelphia, and Norman Echavarria, who
manufactures construction materials, were driving in a car Friday
when they were stopped by the group driving in several vehicles,
police said.
   Police believe Ray's abduction was accidental because apparently
the group's objective was to obtain a ransom for Echavarria.
   However, the businessman's family has not said if the kidnappers
told them of any demands.
   Ray arrived Jan. 17 in Medellin, Colombia's second-largest city,
and was to return to Philadelphia on Monday after visiting
Echavarria.
</TEXT>
