<HEAD>Fire Engulfs Downtown Block</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire engulfed a downtown block
Saturday night in this east Texas town, destroying a number of
businesses, officials said.
   ``Our whole downtown is now on fire,'' said fire dispatcher
Sheila Watson, who later said the fire involved only one of the
three blocks in the downtown district late Saturday night. ``We are
working to keep it from spreading.''
   There were no reports of injuries.
   The fire was reported shortly before 10 p.m. by Tracy Griffin,
manager of the Tradewinds Motel in Jacksonville, a town of 13,000
about 120 miles southeast of Dallas.
   ``It is still out of control and already destroyed one block of
business,'' Betty Ewalt, editor of the Jacksonville Daily Progress,
said at 11:30 p.m.
   Among the businesses destroyed were a department store, three
clothing stores and a bakery.
