<HEAD>Construction Official's Residence Bombed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded Sunday outside a government
official's home, and police said they suspected radicals opposed to
expansion of Tokyo's international airport.
   Neither Katsuhisa Kamijo, 78, acting chairman of the Council for
Public Land Use, nor his wife were injured, said an official of the
