<SECOND>AM-Japan-Markets,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dollar Surges, Stock Prices Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar surged in early trading Monday against
the Japanese yen, while stock prices rose to a new high.
   The dollar opened trading at 129.58 yen, up 0.93 yen from last
Friday's close of 128.65 yen.
   Dealers said the market benefitted from indications U.S. economic
growth remained strong last year. The Commerce Department reported
Friday that U.S. economic growth for 1988 reached 3.8 percent, up
from 3.6 percent in 1987.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which gained 32.94 points to close at a record
31,679.07 points during Saturday's half-day session, added another
64.15 points, or 0.2 percent, to move to 31,743.22 shortly after the
market opened.
</TEXT>
